        Description copied from interface: EventLoggerBuilder.OptionalMethods
        Proved a custom exception handler that will intercept the exception and can then
        Specified by:
        withCustomExceptionHandler in interface EventLoggerBuilder.OptionalMethods<T_EVENT_ACTION extends EventAction,EventLoggerBuilder.ResultSubBuilder<T_EVENT_ACTION extends EventAction,T_RESULT>>
        Parameters:
        exceptionHandler - A function to allow you to provide a different EventAction based on the exception. The skeleton EventAction is passed in to allow it to be copied.
        If null or this method is not called then an outcome will be set on the skeleton event action and the exception message will be added to the outcome description. The outcome success will be set to false.
        In either case, an event will be logged and the original exception re-thrown for the caller to handle. Any exceptions in the handler will be ignored and the original exception rethrown.
        Returns:
        The builder instance.
